##1) Calculate \(\frac{dN}{Ndt}\) ####a) The per capita change in population over time is calculated by the following approximation: \[(1) \ \ \ \frac{dN}{Ndt} = ln(\frac{N_{t+1}}{N_{t}})\] Equation (1) allows us to calculate per capita change over time having only population at time \(t+1\) and \(t\). The natural log is derived from equation (2): \[(2) \ \ \ N_{t+1} = N_t e^{r(1-\frac{Nt}{K})}\]
